@startuml tls-http-transport
' Requirements: L1-SEC-002, L2-SEC-005
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title TLS-Protected HTTP API Transport (production deployment)
autonumber

actor "Client" as CL
participant "Kestrel TLS Endpoint" as TLS
participant "HTTP API" as API

note over CL, API
  L2-SEC-005: GIVEN a production deployment
  WHEN clients connect to API endpoints
  THEN transport is established over TLS.
end note

== TLS handshake ==
CL -> TLS : ClientHello (TLS 1.2+ offered)
activate TLS
TLS --> CL : ServerHello, server certificate, key share
CL -> CL : verify server certificate chain
CL -> TLS : key exchange, Finished
TLS --> CL : Finished (encrypted session established)
deactivate TLS

== HTTPS request over encrypted channel ==
CL -> API : GET /api/instances (over established TLS session)
activate API
API --> CL : 200 OK (response encrypted in transit)
deactivate API

== Cleartext attempt (production) ==
opt client attempts plain http://
  CL -> TLS : cleartext HTTP request
  activate TLS
  TLS --> CL : refused or 307 redirect to https (HSTS enforced)
  deactivate TLS
end
@enduml
